subSubSection.paragraph:
HEMISPERMATOPHORE (
Figs. 32–33
). Long, slender, with a relatively short flagellum. Inner, median and outer lobes well formed, laminate, apically rounded. Inner lobe separated from median and outer lobes, the latter fused. Basal lobe a broad, rounded flange extending over the base of the inner margin of the median lobe (i.e. at the incision separating it from the inner lobe).

